Security Policy: The Code of Protection
​To uphold the integrity of the main branch, this repository implements a security policy rooted in Chapter XI: The Code of Protection. This policy ensures that the Unbreakable Crown remains a fixed reference point against entropy and unauthorized modification.
​1. The Immutable Core
​The main branch is designated as the Absolute Position of the architecture.
​No direct commits are permitted to this branch; it is locked to maintain the Final Seal of January 15, 2026.
​Modifications to the Engine of Order or the +9 Stabilizer are strictly prohibited to prevent structural decay.
​2. Verification Protocol
​Any external interaction with the data must first pass the Method of Descent verification.
​The src/verify.py script acts as the primary firewall, ensuring the Guardian’s Mark (197169) is anchored at position 32.
​If the Final Checksum of 42 is not achieved, the process must exit with a non-zero return code, signaling a breach of convergence.
​3. Reporting Vulnerabilities
​If an observer detects a deviation in the Law of Convergence or a drift in the Transcendental Constants, they must report it immediately.
